What are Tote Bags?
Tote bags are defined by their open‑top design, parallel side handles, and spacious interior, making them ideal for everyday shopping, travel, and promotional use. Their construction can vary widely-from traditional canvas and cotton weaves to premium leather and high‑tech recycled polyester blends-allowing brands to position them either as functional everyday items or as fashion‑forward accessories. In the Asia‑Pacific context, tote bags serve a dual purpose: they act as an environmentally responsible alternative to disposable plastic bags and simultaneously fulfill a growing demand for stylish, reusable personal items.
